<br>
I like ogres. always have, always will. But are they better than trolls? That whole regen thing looks advantageous, at least as far as soloing (uggh) goes. Ogre not getting stunned is great also, even my fatboy shaman doesn't get stunned front on. And their str/stamina is great. So my question is, assuming that ogres make great warriors, the starting stats must be important in some way, so what would you experienced warriors reccomend? As a shaman, generally you put everything you can on wis, and tack the other 5 points somewhere. But I don't want to regret 30 levels later having screwed up the starting stats.<br>
<br>
Posting on my lunchbreak is bad cause the damn boss keeps interrupting me and throwing out my concentration, so appologies for the disjointed post...<br>
<br>
<br>
